    {
        "content": "<p>Unification goes from left to right</p>",
        "id": 558899752,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1763909398
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So with foo we get first <code>?p =?= (a, b)</code> which unifies <code>?p := (a, b)</code> and then we get <code>a =?= (a, b).fst</code> and <code>b =?= (a, b).snd</code> which both work</p>",
        "id": 558899892,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1763909518
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but with bar we get first <code>a =?= Prod.fst ?p</code> which gets stuck</p>",
        "id": 558899936,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1763909563
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>that's my guess</p>",
        "id": 558899938,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1763909569
